*** Latest Update --> Health + Forced Delay PRESS 'L' to switch ***
0-9 -        Change Block Type
Click -     Mine or Place block
WASD -  Walk/Swim Left, right, up and down
E -          Open Inventory, or a chest/crafting table/furnace if the
              cursor is over one when pressed.  E again to close.
Space -   Drop a single tile from a stack while dragging
              or pick up a single block if held when mouse clicked.

Apologies to those who think there's too much minecraft in the world.  It just happens to be a rather useful example to tiled gameplay taken to the max.  So there you go.

*** History ***

So what started out as a little break from Scratchnapped to test a new approach I'd thought of to tiled scrolling has now swelled in to another hefty project, which I have to say I am enjoying immensely, a 2D Minecraft Clone! To achieve the scrolling, unlike in scratchnapped, I create a grid of sprites (whether the tile has something there or not), and as the sprites move off one side of the screen I swap their costumes and move them to the opposite side...  It's probably the fastest way of moving an entire screen of tiles that I have found thus far...  How do you find it?

EDIT: I know the rules are complicated ���~��� Sorry not sorry
project_instructions:
RULES
   Act as miner running an operation to collect Carbon (C), Iron (Fe), 
Silver (Ag), Gold (Au), and Plutonium (Pu)
   Carbon and Iron appear randomly on the board, simply pass over them to collect. Then, go to the chest in the top right corner and press SPACE to add it to your inventory.
   Then, you can drag the metals from your inventory into another metal to FUSE, or to the shop to SELL. Each metal can be fused from the two metals before it.
  
  In order to FUSE, you must drag one metal from your inventory and drop it on another. It does not matter which metal you drag. 
  FOR EXAMPLE: If you drag Carbon to Iron OR Iron to Carbon, it will both make silver. Below are the recipes for more metals:
 
 C + Fe = Ag
  Fe + Ag = Au
  Ag + Au = Pu

Prices for Selling -
 C - $1
 Fe - $3
 Ag - $6
 Au - $10
 Pu - 17

project_description:
It seems that sprite touch testing with Stage3D enabled causes a slowdown for the subsequent screen refresh. The more objects there are testing for touching (e.g. lots of clones), the bigger the slowdown.

Note that it doesn't appear to be the touching test itself that is slow – the time for that remains practically zero. It's the refresh *after* the touching test that is slow. (BUT... see inside, and set either the "do touch test" custom block [in cat sprite], or the "test" custom block [in red circle sprite] to run without refresh... Huh?!)

Also, it's worse if the clones have different looks as I've done here (e.g. different sizes/directions/effects) – making them all look the same significantly reduces the slowdown.

The opposite test (getting the red circle to test if touching clones) also causes a slowdown if the clones have different looks.

Switching off Stage3D (ctrl-M/cmd-shift-M) avoids slowdown.

Really don't know why all of that would be the case...  :/
project_title: Stage3D slow refresh after touch sprite test

project_description:
I have wanted to make this MAP for SO LONG!!! :DDDDDDD
I thought it was a brilliant idea, since Asgore is literally collecting jars of hearts (SOULs). And then Toriel isn't just infuriated, but heartbroken, and wants to do everything she can to protect fallen children.
-----
So, the idea of this is that Toriel broke up with her husband Asgore a long time ago. (It's a long story.) Now, Asgore is trying to win her back, and she's telling him that it's never going to happen, because he broke her heart and killed the children she took care of.
The main character is Toriel, and Asgore is also rather important.
The background characters you can (and probably should) use are Frisk, Sans, the fallen humans/SOULs, Chara, and Asriel.
-----
RULES:
- PLEASE, PLEASE follow the real palettes/sprites for the characters! I included the sprites for Toriel and Asgore in the project so you'd have a reference, so if you want to include a background character, you can find their sprite and upload it.
- This is NOT a Soriel MAP. Please don't include anything Soriel related! (Not just because I don't like it, it's just not the focus here.)
- DO NOT steal art from other Scratchers. If I see you doing this, I will delete your part and exclude you from the MAP.
- This is a PMV MAP, since I thought it would be a little easier. You an include small animated loops, like walking or talking, but nothing big.
- Real codeword is your favorite Undertale ship! (My personal faves are Alphyne, NicePants, and Asgoriel!)
- There is no deadline, but I would appreciate if you had your part(s) done within a few months! (If you don't have it done by January 2019, tho, that's a different story XD)
- Limit of 3 parts!
- For this MAP, I would like for you to have some experience. I will check your projects if you ask for a part.
- I know I already said this, but I can't stress it enough. PLEASE use the sprites of the characters as references!
- Don't be rude/insult other people's parts. I've never had trouble with this, but still.
- Codeword is inside the project!
-----

Minesweeper is a game of hidden mines.  When the game starts, you will see a grid of blank tiles.  Hidden below each tile is one of the following:
 - A mine
   If you reveal a mine, it explodes and it's game over for you.
 - A blank
   If you reveal a blank cell, you earn +5 points for each blank cell.
 - A number
   Number cells indicate the number of neighboring mines touching
   this cell, including diagonal neighbors.  For example, a 1 means
   this cell is touching exactly 1 mine.  A 3 means this cell is
   touching exactly 3 mines.  Etc.  Revealing number cells also
   earns +5 points.

The goal of the game is to discover where the mines are located and flag them.  If you think a cell is a mine, hold <Space> and click the cell to flag that cell as having a mine below it.  If you think a cell is not a mine, click it to reveal what's behind the tile.

There are ten hidden mines and once you have correctly flagged all ten, you win the game.  Good luck!

12/1/15 :o 1000 views!!! Sorry I've been so slow on updating this but you guys seem to be having fun and that's all I need to hear. I've really enjoyed how much this fandom has grown since I started this project, and I look forward to sharing more stories and experiences with you :D

12/12/15 2...000...views. Wow. That was fast. Apparently I've done something right, with, uh, putting so much effort into this. Heh, it's just always so nice seeing people pop up into my message feed, knowing that they're a conscious being, and seeing that they love and seek to understand my project. So, once again, thank you all :3

12/19/15 3000 views. That was fast. You probably expect me to say something. ...I won't. I'll type it :D This project has become one of the biggest Undertale projects for reasons I can't understand (considering there are so many others out there), and I love it whenever someone praises or offers criticism on my coding and design ^^ This feeling...of acceptance...it is what I am experiencing right now! So...uh...before this becomes a wall of text, thanks again c:

Minesweeper is a game of hidden mines.  When the game starts, you will see a grid of blank tiles.  Hidden below each tile is one of the following:
 - A mine
   If you reveal a mine, it explodes and it's game over for you.
 - A blank
   If you reveal a blank cell, you earn +5 points for each blank cell.
 - A number
   Number cells indicate the number of neighboring mines touching
   this cell, including diagonal neighbors.  For example, a 1 means
   this cell is touching exactly 1 mine.  A 3 means this cell is
   touching exactly 3 mines.  Etc.  Revealing number cells also
   earns +5 points.

The goal of the game is to discover where the mines are located and flag them.  If you think a cell is a mine, hold <Space> and click the cell to flag that cell as having a mine below it.  If you think a cell is not a mine, click it to reveal what's behind the tile.

There are ten hidden mines and once you have correctly flagged all ten, you win the game.  Good luck!

Description of Clutterfunk:
   Clutterfunk introduces the size portals, which shrink and expand the player's size. It also introduces spinning sawblades of three sizes along with fake sawblades as a decoration of four sizes and two new block designs. It is the only level to end as a mini cube.

Secret Coins:
   The first secret coin is located at 30% and is collected as the ship. After switching from a mini cube into the ship, players must aim to carefully fly just above the 5th obstacle to reach the coin.
   The second secret coin is located at 65% and is also collected as the ship. After the ship switches gravity, the player must aim low and avoid the saw blade and carefully go through a 1-block wide opening to get the coin. A light tap is required to drop to the saw blade on the bottom.
    The third coin is located at 85% and is collected as the cube. The player must fall past the last yellow jump ring and jump along a tight path to grab the coin. Tapping a blue jump ring rebounds the player to the normal path.

Info:
 Difficulty - Insane
Level Number - 11
Stars - 11
Award in Normal - A ship with a point on the peak, and a booster that looks like a crater on the side.
Award in Practice - The Color Purple
First appeared - 1.4
Previous Level - X-Step
Next level - Theory of Everything
Song by - Waterflame
Introduces - Mini portals
Time to Complete - 1 min, 36-39 sec

What's new:

  Clutterfunk has been added to the Lite version of Geometry Dash, when the new Level Fingerdash was added to 2.1

project_description:
Controls:
1-4 to add a rope 1-4 segments long
5 to add a black hole

Other:
z to apply a custom horizontal force to the end of the ropes
x to jiggle the ropes
c to hide/show the cat's stats
v to attach a rocket to the ends of the ropes with custom force.
b to remove the rockets
d to 'erase' black holes
f to add TnT

==+==+==+[}==+==+==+[}==+==+==+[}==+==+==()[}

Stats:
Black holes are assumed to have a mass of 1, with the same being true of the Scratch Cat.

Ropes also have a mass of one, with a gravity of 1, and a friction of 0.7, when taunt. Ropes also can pass energy upwards, at a dampening rate of 0.3. The ropes also are a clone of the Scratch Cat; that cuts down on a gravity custom block!

When gravity's affect on an object is being computed, the distance is skewed by +2 so as to stop objects from getting velocities of 2,000+.

Rockets have no mass, though they are the rope clones, just showing vs. their previous hiding.

A fun fact about ropes is that they act like pendulums; who knew!

TnT works like a white hole; basically, it figures out its own gravity, reverse it, and calls that the explosion. Due to it being feeble, I made the 'gravity constant' equal 20,000 for explosions. Also, the distance is skewed by 1, not the old 2.

==+==+==+[}==+==+==+[}==+==+==+[}==+==+==()[}

Update log:

v.0.8.5 brings:
1). A small cut on CPU load with ropes.
2). A test with real-life pendulum physics, which ended up failing. The code is still there, if anyone wants to look, and if they can.
3). A bug fix with deleting black holes.

v.0.8.2 brings:
1). I solved a problem that's been giving me a headache for awhile...  also, more realistic rope physics. I will be testing out another model for ropes soon.

v.0.7.8 brings:
1). Simplified ropes. These scripts will be used in my upcoming Scratch game: Cut the Rope! It won't be my next project though; my Spanish homework/project will be. 

v.0.7.7 brings:
1). The cat now experiences friction.
2). TnT! Just press f.
3). The key d.

v.0.7.4 brings:
1). Improved rope physics; they don't act like a series of springs now, but rather a free falling object&pendulum.
2). Rockets point left if their force is negative; thanks to a friend for suggesting that!
3). A few bug fixes!
4). Next will be d; the delete key!

v.0.6.6 brings:
1). Rockets to help me test the rope physics once improved...
2). A few slight changes.

v.0.6.5 brings:
1). A few touch ups.

v.0.6.4 brings:
1). Improved rope physics!
2). A few new keys; try em!
3). Ropes now reflect their velocity through their color&shade.

v.0.5.6 brings:
1). Ropes!

v.0.4.0 brings:
1). Gravity, music, and the cat!

==+==+==+[}==+==+==+[}==+==+==+[}==+==+==()[}

Credits to:
1). Kevin Macleod for the music!
2). A real life friend for a suggestion.
project_instructions:
Just my sandbox on physics. In here, you'll find various things, from my ever-developing rope engine (which is planned to go into the Wiki once finished), to black holes. This is more of an simulation then a game, though I hope you'll still enjoy!

Also, please post your reactions to how you think the engine works; all feedback is appreciated!

project_instructions:
Drücke die Leertaste, um den Keil fallen zu lassen und die Holzstücke zu zerstören. Desto höher der rote Pfeil in der oberen, linken Ecke des Bildschirms ist, desto schneller fällt der Keil. Kaufe Upgrades, um den Keil besser und schneller zu machen. Du musst alle Hölzer eines Levels zerstören, um das nächste Level zu erreichen. Wenn Du mehr als 50% der Hölzer eines Levels zerstörst, erhältst Du 2 Münzen, wenn Du alle zerstörst, gibt es noch mehr Münzen. Momentan gibt es 13 Level, mehr sind in Planung. Du kannst zusätzlich Powerups kaufen, um noch mehr Hölzer zu zerstören.

Knöpfe:
Der Knopf mit dem Pokal lässt alle gewonnenen Trophäen erscheinen.
Drücke auf den Knopf mit dem Keil, um deinen Holzkeil zu verbessern.
Der Knopf mit dem Pfeil öffnet den Powerup-Laden. 
Drücke den Knopf im unteren Teil des Meüs, um ein Level zu spielen. Nach Abschließen eines Levels öffnet sich das Hauptmenü automatisch.

Teacups: 50 sun. Produces Sun.
Adorable thing: 50 sun. Blocks off zombies.
Farty pusheen: 100. sun Shoots toots at zombies.
Snow kitty: 175 sun. Shoots snow that slows down zombies.
Nyanopeater: 200 sun. Shoots two rainbow peas at once.
Bomb: 150 sun. Explodes after you place it.

-Zombies can eat cats

-Grid placing system

The music used in this project is from Mega Man, and the background sprites are also from Mega Man. Thank you for watching. :)
project_instructions:
What's this?!? An intro for a fan-made robot master AND extra animations?!? It can't be true!

Needless to say, it is true, and here for you now. This is a robot master I designed myself, by drawing him out on paper, and creating 8-bit sprites for him on MS Paint. I made this intro to look like the boss intro from the original Mega Man.

-Solder Man Stats- (Pronounced as: SAH-DER)

Reason for Creation: Made to work in an industrial factory 
Weapon: Soldering Iron (S. Iron) A weapon that sticks out of the buster, and remains in front of the user until the button is released. When released, it will travel in a straight line at top speed. It will drain energy gradually while touching enemies, and subtract even more when fired. After being released, it will do more damage than usual
Weakness: Polar Freeze
Friends: None, due to his cold and dark personality
Rivals/Enemies: Main enemy is mankind, and all that associate with it in any way
Hobbies: None; all he does is sulk around his factory, hitting things with his Soldering Iron out of anger

More Background Info: Solder Man is one of the oldest existing robot masters in the known world. At his job, Solder Man was a hard-working yet kind machine. However, when a new industrial revolution took place, the factory where Solder Man worked was shut down. Before he could be taken away and scrapped, though, Solder Man's personality took a dark turn and became unapproachable and dangerous. For many decades, he roamed his factory as a lonely robot, and vowed never to work for another human again. When Wily invaded the abandoned factory, Solder Man tried to retaliate using self-defense, but was easily shut down, captured, and modified for combat.
project_title: Mega Man Boss Bash 2 - Solder Man Animations

project_description:
*** Latest Updates ***

Shameless Advert - Super scrolling tiled minecraft test project with animated Steve: http://scratch.mit.edu/projects/12738968/

13-05-2013 - Update to WIP level designer sandbox - remix the following project and I can see your levels - perhaps we could even collab? http://scratch.mit.edu/projects/10126649

10-05-2013 - Woohoo, Scratch 2 is officially live! :) - I've updated the scripts to try to get rid of the bug where moving platforms did not reappear on level 3... It's an annoying one because it's never happened to me, but I can understand how it might, so I've tried a fix!

03-05-2013 - Have a play with my Work In Progress Level Editor here: http://beta.scratch.mit.edu/projects/10126649/ - This is actually the latest work in progress version of this project and will be merged back in with this one in time... I didn't want to do that yet though in case I'd broken anything with the changes!

02-05-2013 - More changes to level spawning / scrolling code + New type of moving platform (controllable) + Changes to level 4... A little easier now? But hopefully still just as fun + Progress flags do not de-flag as other flags are reached.

01-05-2013 - Bit of another code rearrange with regard to level scrolling. I've changed to have a larger despawn range compared to the standard just off screen spawning of tiles. This means there are more sprites to be handled at a time, but less to create and delete when hanging around the same location. Also, deletion is handled better... I'm hoping this will rid us of the horrid disappearing bug.

30-04-2013 - Fixed group pounding on to moving platforms + death while completing level + Prevented moving platforms from despawning so they will always come back ;)

30-04-2013 - Level 4 added - Try it out now! This one will require a lot more skill to complete, and A LOT of skill to collect all the coins. It will definitely not stay as level 4 is it is too difficult for so early on in the game :)

29-04-2013 - Added way points and restored enemies and coins to point of last save. Added extra lives to be collected as alternative to coins when enemies are killed (depending on the number of lives you have left).

29-04-2013 - Reduced Scratches momentum a little, enable scratch to jump off of enemies when bouncing on their heads. Reduced number of coins on 2nd level to improve performace.

29-04-2013 - Stopped just off screen sprites from animating costumes needlessly.

28-04-2013 - Fixed group pound bugs in small areas.

27-04-2013 - Removed flashing 'next' from title page. Prevent group pound in small contained areas causing glitch. Prevent ground pound on exit from level.

26-04-2013 - Performance Improvements - Clouds don't drift any more, but perhaps you never noticed anyhow? ;)
26-04-2013 - Introduced moment of friction that pulls scratch to a halt when his momentum is less than a critical amount and he's on the ground.
26-04-2013 - Increased Scratches ability to change his direction in the air. Let me know whether this improves things for you or hinders you - Thanks!
26-04-2013 - Fixed spelling errors on intro ;)

*** Known Issues ***

If you are experiencing bad performance then you might consider trying it in firefox (it doesn't appear to suffer the same low framerate issues as chrome when holding down keys on slower computers).

*** Credits for Music and Sound effects ***

Many thanks to the amazing sound artists out there letting people use their work under the creative commons license - Thank you!!!

*** Music ***

Itty Bitty 8 Bit by Kevin MacLeod - http://goo.gl/TF3UM

*** Sounds ***

Foot step sounds by swuing - http://goo.gl/eYn3o
Unprocessed Grunts by Sruddi1 - http://goo.gl/V02qP
Boing by juskiddink - http://goo.gl/w76oW
Pop by mlestn1 - http://goo.gl/mVK1D
Collect Sound by fins - http://goo.gl/CzwfA
project_instructions:
* Suffering from lag? - If so you might try Firefox (chrome bug?).

* Aim - Rescue all the Scratchlings (1 per level)... Thus far there's only 4 levels (This is a demo/preview - As I add new features these will be fleshed out and more added).

* Controls - Cursor keys to move (left & right), up to jump. down while in the air to ground pound. Jump against a wall then jump again to wall jump/kick. If near the top ledge of a wall Scratch will cling on (from where you can either climb up, jump off or drop down).

Notes - See how many coins you can collect on your way, and whether you can get that possibly hidden or hard to get to Mega Coin on each level.  Some baddies can be stomped on, prickly ones and spiders can't (at present).  Don't fall off the bottom of the level... instant life lost.

There's so much more for me to add, and the levels will become a lot better as time goes by, but I am just dying for some feedback to all the work I have put in to this :) - I think you will like it!

Please note - This is not the finished game and some aspects are a little rushed compared to others...  Feel free to comment :)  I only just added the mario like bricks and blocks seen on the first level, see how you can head them to kill enemies above?  You won't see these anywhere else in the game so far as I haven't made further use of them yet.  I'm going to make a lot more of the scores and level time, later too :)

project_description:
This work has been inspired by the work of novice27b.  I wanted to illustrate the attractor in a 3D environment. Thank you!

The 3D interface is a based on a projection algorithm I developed some years ago to make Geometer's Sketchpad display 3D curves.
I learned a tremendous amount from @Mr_Pyro_ 3D Wireframe Engine project about optimizing rendering and keyboard effects.  Much much thanks.
project_instructions:
This demo employs a 3D interface to display a portion of the Lorenz Attractor.  The attractor demonstrates the chaotic evolution of simplified weather system and how the slightest modification in the initial conditions would lead to vastly different endgames, commonly known as the Butterfly Effect.

Up/Down Right/Left arrows and a/z keys rotate the object along the x,y,z axis.

project_description:
After a LONG time of working, the sequel to Defcon One is finished! With graphics and some mechanics based on "Tank Game" by Tankgame123, this version includes:

-Smoother and more fluent controls!
-Better fighting engine!
-Tons of new weapons!
-Awesome new sound effects!
-Much better graphics!
I hope you enjoy! As always, no need to rate, but please give me some ideas on what to improve! Have fun!
project_instructions:
Red Tank: WASD keys to move. Press Space to fire, Q to place a land mine, and E to fire a rocket!
Blue Tank: Arrow Keys to move, press 0 to fire, 8 to place a land mine, and 9 to fire a rocket!
First person to destroy the other tank by depleting their health completely wins!
Colliding into each other kills both of you and will result in a draw.

- Character select is different

- C will give you points (for cheaters)

- Changed price of Springtrap 
- Changed a few layouts

- Phantom BB jump-scare
- New logo

- Old Bonnie hard mode added
- Springtrap hard mode added
- Nightmare Bonnie hard mode added
- New menu layout
- Extras menu
- Achievement menu
- Nerfing with the mask  
- New achievements
- New ending
- FNAF 4 doors
- Stars

- A few other minor things

- Other minor things

- Tutorial

project_description:
RedNeckSideKick did a great job to start at the SPARK programming session. Working with him and Secondo we have now added two motion modes (Terrestrial and Space) that can be clicked and the cross screen boundaries.

Learned a bit about race conditions in testing for collisions.
project_instructions:
Work in progress (instruction further down after this brief message)...
Things remaining to do are as follows:
1. Need to ensure the regeneration of ship does not land in middle of collision (gets annoying to loose a couple of ships that way in early levels). Similar logic to hyper drive (finding open field with largest available space)
2. Need to add bonus items (alien ships(done), shooting stars, etc) to get either extra points, limited shields, teleport (hyper drive), extra fuel.
3. Added risk items (a special alien death ship that is reflective to bounce laser back)… (done)
4. Need to add fuel limit per ship (adrift in space mode)
5. Need to adjust asteroid speed to be in proportion to size (smaller are faster)
6. Fracture angle should be somewhat randomized
7. Need asteroids to adjust trajectory when they collide (no fracture)
8. Twinkle background
9. Use sprites for points, level, and highscore (i.e., need number sprites 0…9)
10. List of initials for highest 10 scores.

Current Instructions:
Use the arrow keys (up, down, left, right) to move the ship forward, backward, turn left, turn right.
Use the space bar to fire.

New ship for each level cleared, but limited to maximum number of ships depending on mode selected. Level = number of starting asteroids. In Terrestrial mode the motion is single-step (high friction) with 1/10/100 points for asteroid sizes, 4 ships to start with a 5 ship limit. In Space mode the motion is space-like and things can get insane quickly (in space no one can hear you scream); points are 10/100/1000 with 8 ships to start and a 10 ship limit.
Watch and Enjoy!

project_description:
I used the assistance of my Professor, the Scratch Programs he provided, and some common sense in the making of this game. The hardest part of the project was determining how the sprite was to attack the monsters. Clearly the sprite itself could not touch the monsters, as that was supposed to cause a life to be lost, yet clearly the sprite had to somehow come in contact with the monster to "kill" it. After playing around for a while, I came across the idea to use a different sprite, one that was attached to the Link sprite at the hip, but was not part of the Link sprite, and could therefore touch the monster without losing a life. Therefore the attack sprite, or sprite 1 was born. It took quite a bit of fiddling, but eventually I was able to make the sprite do what I wanted after also slightly modifying the Link sprite. While this part of the project was a challenge, it was still quite an enjoyable experience. The second most time consuming part of the project was cropping all of the Link sprites for walking and attacking from 4 different directions. That took a substantial amount of time and energy, but I believe that the end product is worth the time invested. 

There should be sounds if you win or lose, as well as if you kill a monster or lose a life.

Player 1 (Frisk): Use arrow keys to move. Dodge the things for as long as you can. If you see a blue line don't move while passing through it and you won't take damage. If it's orange it's the opposite of the blue, move and you won't take damage.

Player 2 (Enemy): Use Q W E A S D Z X and C to activate each individual attack. Q for the dots, W for the lines, E for the blue/orange line, A for the Circle, S for the upper sweeper, D for the lower sweeper, Z for the gaster blaster, X for the strange laser, and C for the turrets. Press F to end your turn, and Space to switch enemy sprites. Use r for Frog Hop attack.

GUYS MAKE SURE TO HIT THAT HEART BUTTON AND LEAVE A COMMENT DOWN BELOW 

 ======= Change Log
✯ 27 Dec 2016 ♒ Single player version released, beginning work on multiplayer version...
✯ 26 Dec 2016 ♒ XP Meter goes by total xp ratio, not by restarting xp points.
✯ 26 Dec 2016 ♒ XP needed for animals has been lowered, once again, for easier access to higher animals.
✯ 26 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch where certain objects show in front of the map.
✯ 23 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch where crocs+ when going under water spots, appear on top.
✯ 22 Dec 2016 ♒ You can now squeeze through small openings after dashing forward.
✯ 22 Dec 2016 ♒ Changed order of animals. Mole is now before fox and cheetah before lion.
✯ 21 Dec 2016 ♒ Underwater bubbles and underground textures now fall underneath trees and items on the map.
✯ 16 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed mole glitches!
✯ 15 Dec 2016 ♒ Berry bushes are now smaller and berries will now spawn more like the real game.
✯ 15 Dec 2016 ♒ Lowered the mushroom bush hit distance, once again.
✯ 15 Dec 2016 ♒ Changed the location of some stones that spawned in strange places.
✯ 14 Dec 2016 ♒ "XP to Next Animal" X Location fits to new lowered xp for upgrades.
✯ 12 Dec 2016 ♒ Foods' XP given now holds true to the original game and, also, XP needed for animals has been lowered for easier access to the higher animals.
✯ 12 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed bear hill glitch and changed colors of objects to fit the style of the original game.
✯ 12 Dec 2016 ♒ Order of animals changed: Mole now comes before deer.
✯ 11 Dec 2016 ♒ Added dragon!!!
✯ 10 Dec 2016 ♒ Added rhino and hippo! Also, adjusted mushroom bush hit physics to not move so far away after being hit.
✯ 10 Dec 2016 ♒ Added crocodile and adjusted animal speeds.
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Finally fixed glitch that still allowed you to get stuck in a hill despite previous attempts at fixing the glitch.
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Bears can now climb through hills!
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitches relating to extra large sized outlines on higher animals.
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Mushroom bush update! Mushroom bushes have been completely remodeled. Bugs fixed, smoother engine, more true to the original game. They're much more fun to eat now!
✯ 8 Dec 2016 ♒ Mushrooms/lillypads now move if you touch them when below the needed animal to eat them.
✯ 8 Dec 2016 ♒ It is now possible to die of thirst!
✯ 7 Dec 2016 ♒ XP Points Meter is now much smoother. It slides as you gain XP. Looks better.
✯ 7 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch that made you get stuck in a hill after coming out of a hole toward a hill.
✯ 3 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch that made the game lag a bit moments after clicking the green flag. + mini map details finished!
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ 50% done with mini map details (in top right corner of screen...)
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Changed speed of mole underground so that it moves at a constant speed even in mud.
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Added "Air" bar while underground as a mole. Also, moles can no longer jump forward while underground.
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Added "Air" bar while underwater. (Limits the time you can stay underwater.)
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Added smooth animation to berries/water drops when eaten.
✯ 1 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch where you could eat mushrooms/berries while underwater or underground.
✯ 1 Dec 2016 ♒ Moles can now dig underground! Hold W or SPACE while in a hole to dig underground around the map. Moles can no longer swim underwater.

project_description:
!! OMIGOSH GUYS, YOU'RE ALL TOO AMAZING-- !!

Yes, as you may know, I returned from Hawaii half an hour ago (more like left the jetport than Hawaii- I collapsed in baggage claim--)! It was truly spectacular! I'll do my best to go into as much detail as can be, although it is hard because I haven't slept in 42 hours, I crossed six time zones, and I've had the Tangled credit song (Something That I Want... I think?) stuck in my head since I aRriVEd iN haWaII.

~HIGHLIGHT OF MY VACATION~
Definitely swimming in the beautiful, crystal clear waters around O'ahu and Maui and enjoying my time in amazing resorts. 
aLSO I watched Tangled a lot, so I think I have an addiction-

~SCARIEST PART OF MY VACATION~
I got in a car accident! yAY! We were in Maui looking for ice cream and shopping, when we were hit behind by a young couple who quickly fled the scene. We weren't hurt, and the rental car only had a scratch, but fleeing the scene is illegal, childs! We mccalled the police so everything's USDA grade A awesome! :")

More projects coming soon! Thank you so, SO much for 1,060 overwhelming and amazing messages to brighten up my day! AND WAIT, 2K FOLLOWERS?! ARE 'YA JOKING?! You all are so amazing, I wish I could hug every one of you! <33

Detailed Results: http://pulljosh.com/r/UTTT-results/

How the bots were scored:
Each bot played against every other bot 12 times. Half of the time (6 games) one bot went first, and half the time the other bot went first. This means each bot played a total of 36 games. One win counted as 1 point. A tie was 1/2 point, and a loss was 0 points. The bot that scored the most points was the winner.

project_instructions: Just follow the in-game instructions.

Minesweeper is a game of hidden mines.  When the game starts, you will see a grid of blank tiles.  Hidden below each tile is one of the following:
 - A mine
   If you reveal a mine, it explodes and it's game over for you.
 - A blank
   If you reveal a blank cell, you earn +5 points for each blank cell.
 - A number
   Number cells indicate the number of neighboring mines touching
   this cell, including diagonal neighbors.  For example, a 1 means
   this cell is touching exactly 1 mine.  A 3 means this cell is
   touching exactly 3 mines.  Etc.  Revealing number cells also
   earns +5 points.

The goal of the game is to discover where the mines are located and flag them.  If you think a cell is a mine, hold <Space> and click the cell to flag that cell as having a mine below it.  If you think a cell is not a mine, click it to reveal what's behind the tile.

There are ten hidden mines and once you have correctly flagged all ten, you win the game.  Good luck!

project_description: Here's Part 11! At last! Now, on to my other MAP part...
project_instructions:
I decided to start another MAP! This is a MAP about Wings of Fire deaths.

*spoilers*

RULES *please read!* ~

- Your part can be PMV or AMV style, it doesn't really matter.

- You need to have read the book that your part is from. For example, if you want to do Carnelian’s death, you need to have read at least up to Moon Rising. 

- Put the correct death scene in your part!

- Everyone is welcome! If you want to join, comment below and tell me what part you want. The codeword is at the bottom.

- Remix this project with your part.

- Don't use forever loops, and don't animate the backdrop.

- Don't use too much blood, and no gore. I know this is a deaths MAP, but try to keep it Scratch-appropriate.

- You don't have to send me links to any animations/artwork. I'll check your profile.

- Don't use too many sprites -- it makes it too laggy when all the parts are put together! Keep it one background and 1-2 sprites.

- ALL PARTS ARE DUE OCTOBER 15th. No exceptions. If you can't get your part done by then, tell me so I can give it to a backup. If you have your part almost but not quite done, share it and I'll finish it myself.

- You can have as many parts as you want. However, I'd prefer it if you only have one or two unfinished parts.

- Don't insult anyone else's parts.

- Please make sure your animation fits the length of the part. Don't just animate half of it and leave the rest of it frozen, or don't have your animation go over and be longer than the part.

- Backups are always appreciated! If you don't feel comfortable animating a whole part, ask to be a backup instead.

- Follow all the information on the inside of the project as well.


- Codeword: How many sprites you're allowed to have! >:3

project_description:
This is an idea that i came up with and was just starting out in javascript. I originally made it for Khan Academy, but it didn't work the way i wanted it to, so I gave up on it. But recently I've been tinkering around in scratch, and got used to the tools and up until now, I've had a hard time with layers because there was no sort of layer management system... BUUUUT, I've working with the pen tool and realized that, with the code blocks I use for it, there is a fixed layer system, and that I could place things exactly where I wanted to. so yeah its been fun.
Thnx goes out tooo... "tbpatj" for his 3D engine tutorial, it really helped (I know, I know, a 3D project isn't the best thing to start out with)

project_description:
Cubelo, a game of skill,
by joshrawesome

*Please do not use full-screen*

Thanks for Top-Loved!

Instructions:
~ Use the arrow keys (or WASQ) to control your character through 15 levels
~ When you step off of your current block, it will fall
~ Make every block fall before completing the level
~ Block Guide (in order you find them in):
- Blue: Normal block, once you step off it will fall
- Green: Goal, after making every block fall, step onto this one
- Spike: Will go up and down, be careful and don't hit it!
- Grey: After stepping off once, it will turn into a blue block!
- Orange: As soon as you step on to it, it will start to break!
- Yellow: The spike will move up or down every time you move!
- Arrow: Moves you one step in that direction, doesn't affect yellow
~ Have fun!

"You don't fail when you aim high and miss; you fail when you aim low, and you hit."
- Laurence Lewars

(Ecliptic warning D:) <--- ahhhhhhhhh so much lightsssss (XD)
My gang has been back now, woooooooo

Can you identify each character's theme on dah background? o3o

Ocs (in dah gang, ayy):
Coral ♀
Luna♀
Ruby♀
Dadryne♂

*** Currently runs far better in IE & firefox than Chrome *sob* ***
O -          That's the letter O, to save your game
1 to 9 -    Change Block in hand
Click -     Mine or Place block
WASD -  Walk/Swim Left, right, up and down
E -          Open Inventory, chest, crafting table, furnace or door!
Space -   Drop a single tile from a stack while dragging.
F -          Eat food (whatever you are holding at the time)
P -          Pause game (P again to unpause)
T -          Talk - Enter something to say, or type a command:

*** Commands ***
/gamemode 0 -  Switches to survival (works with 0, s or survival)
/gamemode 1 -  Switches to creative (works with 1, c or creative)
/gamemode 4 -  Switches to peaceful (works with 4, p or peaceful)
/time set day -   Changes time of day to morning.
/time set night - Changes time of day to evening/dusk.
/kill -                   Kills you and causes you to re-spawn.
/lighting 0 -        Turns off the lighting effect (for speed)
/lighting 1 -        Turns on the lighting effect (much preferred)
/delay 0 -           Turns off the forced delay - may improve frame rate
                          at the cost of scratch lagging bug...
/delay 2 -           Enable force delay (default)

*** Features ***
* 300 x 80 world (24,000 tiles)
* Full screen tiles scrolling system
* Adaptive Lighting Engine with day/night cycle applied to all tile and entities in the game
* Randomly generated, fully Destructive Terrain/Buildable
* Terrain includes Hills, Valleys, Pools, Trees, Cave systems, Waterfalls + Lavafalls, Beaches and cacti
* Grass spreads across dirt (soil)
* Trees grow from saplings planted on dirt or grass
* Animated player & mobs
* Mining system works with line of sight system working outwards away from player
* Fully working crafting system including inventory crafting and crafting table crafting
* Fully working furnace system for smelting ores and cooking food
* Ignitable exploding TNT
* Sand & Gravel fall when nothing is under them (player suffocation implemented)
* Water & lava flows and current moves player
* Chests contain items
* Player sustains fall damage & has oxygen level bubbles when submerged
* Health replenishes slowly over time
* Blocks that are mined can only be harvested with the correct tool/tool level combination where applicable.
* Preliminary mob code added for Pigs (pig AI allows them to look around, walk, swim, run away and die)
* Customisable Signs can be crafted and written upon
* Digging speed is dependent on tool in use, block type being dug, and level of tool in use (wood, stone, iron, diamond or glass)
* Tools sustain damage when used and wear out
* Items can be used as weapons inflicting greater or lesser amounts of damage depending on tool

*** Implemented blocks ***
Air, Water, Lava
Grass, Dirt, Sand, Clay
Stone, Cobblestone, Sandstone, Gravel, Bedrock, Obsidian
Wood, Leaves, Cactas, Pumpkin*, Sugarcane*
Rose*, Flower*, Mushroom*, Sapling
Cake, Apple, Raw Pork, Cooked Pork, Rotten Flesh
Coal Ore, Diamond Ore, Gold Ore, Iron Ore
Glass, Wood Planks, Stick, Coal, Charcoal, Flint, Diamond, Gold Ingot, Iron Ingot
Chest, Crafting Table, Furnace
Brick, Stone Brick
Ladder, Wooden Door, Bed*, Sign
TNT*, Torch, Flint and Steel
Wooden Shovel, Wooden Axe, Wood Pickaxe, Wooden Sword
Stone Axe, Stone Shovel, Stone Pickaxe, Stone Sword
Iron Shovel, Iron Axe, Iron Pickaxe, Iron Sword
Diamond Shovel, Diamond Axe, Diamond Pickaxe, Diamond Sword
Gold Axe, Gold Shovel, Gold Pickaxe, Gold Sword
Bucket*, Water Bucket*, Lava Bucket*
(* Items with an asterix are not yet attainable except from a chest)

project_description:
~Soap MAP~
_____________________________________________________________
Thank you so much for 50 followers! I'm so happy and thankful for each and everyone of them! Thank you @pandakun for being my 50th follower! So to thank you guys, I am hosting a PMV MAP! 
_____________________________________________________________
This is a semi-experienced PMV pallet MAP. PMV stand for Picture moive video. This means no animating, except for the instrumental parts. You can animate small things but It should not all be animated.
Show me one link of your art and I will respond in the next 48 hours. If you did not get the part, I'm sorry but I will be lenient with the art. Also, if you have done any PMV in the past, that will also give you a better chance of getting the part. If you want an animated part, send me a link to an animation you have made. Good luck!
_____________________________________________________________
Rules:
-PMV style only. You may animate little things if you want. (I will make
an exception for the instrumental part if you want.)
-Follow the pallet!
-Limit yourself to 1-2 sprites (Though I prefer to have 1 just to keep things simple.)
-Everyone gets a month. If you need an extension, I'll give you 2 weeks. After that, you don't get any more time (Sorry :3) 
-Include the lyrics in your part (unless you have an instrumental part)
-You can have a max of 2 parts (3 if I need more parts.)

If you REALLY want to remix, add something interesting! don't just remix and share hoping to get fame. Also, don't remix to make fun of me (Cough, LIKE SOME PEOPLE, cough!)

Here's an animation 
https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/285206076
It's my newest and best one, so I highly suggest that you do! It would mean a lot! also,
this tutorial covers, plot (story) animation, code, and lip sync! As a tip, I would suggest having your OC in your backpack as a sprite, and individual costume, as well as multiple starting poses and/or mouth positions! Thumbnails are good, too! Follow me if you want to see more content!

press space to switch slides.

Two animated examples are included in the project. Instructions to find them are in their respective slides

a love, favorite, and a follow would be much appreciated.

project_description: how to draw a common fool

➳ C o o k i e s

Get a piece of paper and a box of markers, a pencil, and a pen, and click the green flag!
Choose which cookie you want to draw and click the button.
Press space for the next step.
When you are done with your drawing, click the word Done! in the corner to make the next cookie.
Take a picture of your artwork and put it in a remix!
Have fun • ᴗ •

Note: I disliked the way my original gingerbread man turned out, that is why i changed it... if you were wondering.. ._.

Why am i drawing these things? I can't even eat them. I am allergic to chocolate!

Oh well, hope u guys enjoy them anyways :D

I solemnly swear that I am up to no good.
- - - - 

This was my first ever attempt at making a tutorial! It was more complicated than I imagined it would be and I definitely learned a lot in the process. It ended up being a lot of fun to make, though! I'll have to think about what I could focus on for another tutorial in the future ^.^

- - - - - -

Artwork: Created in Illustrator. I used some reference images, which I've shared the links to those below

Wand Concept: Based on the Harry Potter series, specifically involving the Deathly Hallows

Music: Wintergatan - Marble Machine (a musical instrument that uses 2000 marbles! I highly recommend looking up the video if you have not seen it already)

Font: Title font is "Parry Hotter", font inside project is "Lakefont"

Hot glue gun based on: https://pixabay.com/en/tool-hot-glue-gun-glue-gun-hot-glue-159300/

Paint tube based on: https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/school-art-supplies-set-vector-illustration-554329297?src=thmZQjbRVgGN5etF2iNldQ-1-0

project_description:
Edit: OMG FEATURED?!? Thanks so much, I literally jumped out of my skin!!! You guys are wonderful, thanks to the ST for featuring this and thanks to @mathisIZ for suggesting this! <333
Edit #2: Thanks for all the encouraging comments, you guys are making my day. Just a head up, though, I will be deleting any and all comments containing spam and advertisements.
Edit #3: "Off" the front page. Thanks so much for your support everyone! <3

Hello there!
Welcome to my Gradients Tips and Tricks tutorial thing! Wow, I haven't made a tutorial project in so long... Wait a minute, I don't think I've even made a tutorial project before xD

Anyway, welcome to my first tutorial/tips and tricks project! :3 I will be focusing on gradients, and I'll teach you tips and tricks about color schemes, transparent gradients, and more! Use the space bar and the arrow keys to flip through the slides, and use the "m" key to toggle the mouse trail on and off, and use the "n" key to mute and un-mute the music

Level of Difficulty: Beginner / All levels / 
Alevelsoeasyyoumightnotlearnanythingfromthisprojectlol

Please note these tricks may not work in Scratch Bitmap... However, they will work on Scratch 2 and Scratch 3 vector mode! :3

Don't know how to use gradients in Scratch 2? Here's a tutorial!
https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/100740745/

Another tip that I forgot to include is: don't use too vibrant colors in a gradient! :D Try to avoid using the bright color swatches in the Scratch editor.

Record thing:

project_description:
I solemnly swear that I am up to no good.
- - - - 

This was my first ever attempt at making a tutorial! It was more complicated than I imagined it would be and I definitely learned a lot in the process. It ended up being a lot of fun to make, though! I'll have to think about what I could focus on for another tutorial in the future ^.^

- - - - - -

Artwork: Created in Illustrator. I used some reference images, which I've shared the links to those below

Wand Concept: Based on the Harry Potter series, specifically involving the Deathly Hallows

Music: Wintergatan - Marble Machine (a musical instrument that uses 2000 marbles! I highly recommend looking up the video if you have not seen it already)

Font: Title font is "Parry Hotter", font inside project is "Lakefont"

Hot glue gun based on: https://pixabay.com/en/tool-hot-glue-gun-glue-gun-hot-glue-159300/

Paint tube based on: https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/school-art-supplies-set-vector-illustration-554329297?src=thmZQjbRVgGN5etF2iNldQ-1-0

project_instructions:
After four days, this turned out pretty good. I even started a comic that you get to preview at the end of this animation! (Also, the animation/drawings aren't very good because I had to work as fast as I could before school started).

Jasmine is a blue cat, and she doesn't know why. She falls in love with Ebony when he gives her a flower and disappears. She looks all over for him, but she is caught off guard and strong winds blow her into the ocean. She sinks to the city of Atlantis where she wakes up and discovers she's a mermaid. With all this seeming so unreal, Jasmine can't decide whether she's dreaming or it is all real. And if it is a dream, is Ebony a dream, too?

While viewing the pictures at the end, click the pictures to go to the next one.

project_description:
Uses 12 Variables, 6 of which are visible in the game and the other are used in game functionality.

- Credit to Science Olympiad team for the theme and type of game

EDIT: I know the rules are complicated ���~��� Sorry not sorry
project_instructions:
RULES
   Act as miner running an operation to collect Carbon (C), Iron (Fe), 
Silver (Ag), Gold (Au), and Plutonium (Pu)
   Carbon and Iron appear randomly on the board, simply pass over them to collect. Then, go to the chest in the top right corner and press SPACE to add it to your inventory.
   Then, you can drag the metals from your inventory into another metal to FUSE, or to the shop to SELL. Each metal can be fused from the two metals before it.
  
  In order to FUSE, you must drag one metal from your inventory and drop it on another. It does not matter which metal you drag. 
  FOR EXAMPLE: If you drag Carbon to Iron OR Iron to Carbon, it will both make silver. Below are the recipes for more metals:
 
 C + Fe = Ag
  Fe + Ag = Au
  Ag + Au = Pu

Prices for Selling -
 C - $1
 Fe - $3
 Ag - $6
 Au - $10
 Pu - 17

project_instructions:
This is my recreation of the popular game mope.io. This is the sandbox version. 



GUYS MAKE SURE TO HIT THAT HEART BUTTON AND LEAVE A COMMENT DOWN BELOW 

 ======= Change Log
✯ 27 Dec 2016 ♒ Single player version released, beginning work on multiplayer version...
✯ 26 Dec 2016 ♒ XP Meter goes by total xp ratio, not by restarting xp points.
✯ 26 Dec 2016 ♒ XP needed for animals has been lowered, once again, for easier access to higher animals.
✯ 26 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch where certain objects show in front of the map.
✯ 23 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch where crocs+ when going under water spots, appear on top.
✯ 22 Dec 2016 ♒ You can now squeeze through small openings after dashing forward.
✯ 22 Dec 2016 ♒ Changed order of animals. Mole is now before fox and cheetah before lion.
✯ 21 Dec 2016 ♒ Underwater bubbles and underground textures now fall underneath trees and items on the map.
✯ 16 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed mole glitches!
✯ 15 Dec 2016 ♒ Berry bushes are now smaller and berries will now spawn more like the real game.
✯ 15 Dec 2016 ♒ Lowered the mushroom bush hit distance, once again.
✯ 15 Dec 2016 ♒ Changed the location of some stones that spawned in strange places.
✯ 14 Dec 2016 ♒ "XP to Next Animal" X Location fits to new lowered xp for upgrades.
✯ 12 Dec 2016 ♒ Foods' XP given now holds true to the original game and, also, XP needed for animals has been lowered for easier access to the higher animals.
✯ 12 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed bear hill glitch and changed colors of objects to fit the style of the original game.
✯ 12 Dec 2016 ♒ Order of animals changed: Mole now comes before deer.
✯ 11 Dec 2016 ♒ Added dragon!!!
✯ 10 Dec 2016 ♒ Added rhino and hippo! Also, adjusted mushroom bush hit physics to not move so far away after being hit.
✯ 10 Dec 2016 ♒ Added crocodile and adjusted animal speeds.
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Finally fixed glitch that still allowed you to get stuck in a hill despite previous attempts at fixing the glitch.
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Bears can now climb through hills!
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitches relating to extra large sized outlines on higher animals.
✯ 9 Dec 2016 ♒ Mushroom bush update! Mushroom bushes have been completely remodeled. Bugs fixed, smoother engine, more true to the original game. They're much more fun to eat now!
✯ 8 Dec 2016 ♒ Mushrooms/lillypads now move if you touch them when below the needed animal to eat them.
✯ 8 Dec 2016 ♒ It is now possible to die of thirst!
✯ 7 Dec 2016 ♒ XP Points Meter is now much smoother. It slides as you gain XP. Looks better.
✯ 7 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch that made you get stuck in a hill after coming out of a hole toward a hill.
✯ 3 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch that made the game lag a bit moments after clicking the green flag. + mini map details finished!
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ 50% done with mini map details (in top right corner of screen...)
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Changed speed of mole underground so that it moves at a constant speed even in mud.
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Added "Air" bar while underground as a mole. Also, moles can no longer jump forward while underground.
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Added "Air" bar while underwater. (Limits the time you can stay underwater.)
✯ 2 Dec 2016 ♒ Added smooth animation to berries/water drops when eaten.
✯ 1 Dec 2016 ♒ Fixed glitch where you could eat mushrooms/berries while underwater or underground.
✯ 1 Dec 2016 ♒ Moles can now dig underground! Hold W or SPACE while in a hole to dig underground around the map. Moles can no longer swim underwater.

-

Previous updates here: https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/135673470/

project_instructions:
Minesweeper is a game of hidden mines.  When the game starts, you will see a grid of blank tiles.  Hidden below each tile is one of the following:
 - A mine
   If you reveal a mine, it explodes and it's game over for you.
 - A blank
   If you reveal a blank cell, you earn +5 points for each blank cell.
 - A number
   Number cells indicate the number of neighboring mines touching
   this cell, including diagonal neighbors.  For example, a 1 means
   this cell is touching exactly 1 mine.  A 3 means this cell is
   touching exactly 3 mines.  Etc.  Revealing number cells also
   earns +5 points.

The goal of the game is to discover where the mines are located and flag them.  If you think a cell is a mine, hold <Space> and click the cell to flag that cell as having a mine below it.  If you think a cell is not a mine, click it to reveal what's behind the tile.

There are ten hidden mines and once you have correctly flagged all ten, you win the game.  Good luck!
